-- ── aisdr → business-finance (sales) ────────────────────────
('AiSDR', 'aisdr', 'AI sales-development representative — signal-driven prospecting + multichannel sequences (email + LinkedIn + phone) at $900/mo.', 'AiSDR is an autonomous sales-development representative platform that runs the full SDR motion: real-time intent signal hunting via "Live AI search", deep prospect research (LinkedIn activity, company news, industry signals), AI Strategist that generates complete go-to-market campaigns (ICP, messaging angles, sequences) in a 20-minute conversation, multichannel email + LinkedIn + phone sequences with conditional logic, automated lead qualification (handles objections, books meetings only when prospects show genuine interest), and CRM auto-sync. The differentiator vs the AI SDR category is quality-over-volume positioning — AiSDR claims 1-3 qualified meetings per 100 leads and 3-4x higher reply rates than industry averages, with explicit refusal to spam or burn sender domains. Competes with 11x (similar AI SDR positioning), Reply.io (sales-engagement incumbent with AI layer), Smartlead and Instantly (volume-first cold-email tools), Outreach and Apollo (sequencing platforms with newer AI), and Artisan (AI-only SDR play).', 'https://aisdr.com', 'paid', '[{"plan":"Standard","price":"$900/mo (billed quarterly)","features":["Unlimited seats","All features","Live AI search for intent signals","AI Strategist (20-min GTM campaign generation)","Multichannel sequences (email + LinkedIn + phone)","Lead qualification + objection handling","CRM auto-sync","24/7 support","Credit-based model for messages and lead searches"]}]'::jsonb, 'intermediate', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"Live AI search — intent-signal-driven prospecting","Deep research before outreach (LinkedIn + company news + industry signals)","AI Strategist — generates complete GTM campaigns in 20 minutes","Multichannel sequences (email + LinkedIn + phone with conditional logic)","Automated lead qualification + objection handling","CRM auto-sync with contact enrichment","Quality-over-volume positioning (1-3 meetings per 100 leads)","3-4x higher reply rates vs industry averages","Domain reputation protection (refuses spam-volume tactics)"}', '{"HubSpot","Salesforce","LinkedIn","Apollo","Clearbit","Clay","Aircall","Instantly","Zerobounce","Copy.ai","Calendly"}', true, '{"Mid-market sales orgs running outbound that have burnt domains on volume-first tools","Founders and small teams wanting an SDR-in-a-box without hiring","Companies running ABM-style targeted outbound (not spray-and-pray)","Sales teams already on HubSpot or Salesforce who want CRM-native AI SDR"}', '{"Volume-first cold email shops sending 10K+ messages/day (Smartlead / Instantly cheaper)","Solo founders unable to absorb $900/mo minimum spend","Inbound-only revenue motions (no outbound need)","Teams wanting to control the prompt + sequence themselves rather than delegate"}', 'The quality-over-volume AI SDR pick for mid-market teams that have already burnt sender domains on Smartlead or Instantly and want signal-driven outbound that doesn''t spam. AiSDR''s "Live AI search" + 20-minute AI Strategist GTM generation are genuinely differentiated, and the $900/mo flat (unlimited seats) is more honest than per-message pricing. It''s weaker than 11x on enterprise account expansion, weaker than Apollo on raw lead-database breadth, and the $900 floor prices out solo founders. Pick AiSDR when reply-rate quality matters more than message volume; skip if you''re still in the spray-and-pray phase.', now()),

-- ── pangram-labs → research-education ───────────────────────
('Pangram Labs', 'pangram-labs', 'AI content detection — 99.98% accuracy distinguishing human vs AI text across 20+ languages with API and Chrome extension.', 'Pangram Labs is an AI content detection platform with the strongest published accuracy claims in the category — 99.98% accuracy distinguishing human-authored from AI-generated text, with sentence-level highlighting that identifies AI-assisted edits and partial AI generation within otherwise human documents. The product covers AI Segment Analysis (quantifies AI portions inside documents), AI Assistance Detection (highlights AI-edited passages), an integrated plagiarism checker, a Chrome Extension and Google Docs integration for real-time browsing-time detection, batch processing of up to 100 files (PDF, DOCX, RTF), multilingual detection across 20+ languages, and LMS integrations (Canvas, Google Classroom, Moodle, Brightspace). Independent University of Chicago research puts Pangram''s false-positive rate at 0.5% on product reviews vs GPTZero 2.4% and Originality.ai 1.7%. Used by Canvas, Quora, ChatPDF, Newsguard, Wiki Education, LessWrong, and Tremau. Pangram positions against Originality.ai (incumbent in the SEO content niche), GPTZero (academic-first), Copyleaks (enterprise plagiarism + AI detection), Turnitin (academic incumbent), and Winston AI (similar positioning).', 'https://www.pangram.com', 'freemium', '[]'::jsonb, 'beginner', true, '{"web","api","plugin"}', '{"AI Segment Analysis — quantifies AI portions in a document","AI Assistance Detection — highlights AI-edited sections","Integrated plagiarism checker","Chrome Extension + Google Docs integration","Batch processing — up to 100 files (PDF / DOCX / RTF)","Multilingual detection (20+ languages)","REST API for programmatic detection","LMS integrations — Canvas, Google Classroom, Moodle, Brightspace","99.98% claimed accuracy with sentence-level highlighting"}', '{"Canvas","Google Classroom","Moodle","Brightspace","Google Docs","Chrome","REST API"}', true, '{"Universities and academic institutions enforcing AI-use policy in student work","Editorial and journalism teams verifying author authenticity","Content operations enforcing AI-use disclosure on freelancer submissions","Integrity teams at platforms like Newsguard / Quora moderating AI-generated content"}', '{"SEO content shops gaming AI detectors (Originality.ai is the incumbent target)","One-off personal use cases (free tier 4 checks/day is enough)","Buyers wanting public, predictable subscription tier $/mo (homepage hides tiers)","Workflows that don''t care about false-positive rate (cheaper detectors are fine)"}', 'The most accurate AI-content detector in the category for buyers who actually care about false positives — Pangram''s 0.5% FPR (Chicago-verified) is materially better than GPTZero''s 2.4% and Originality.ai''s 1.7%. The Chrome extension + LMS integrations make it the natural pick for academic and editorial use. It''s weaker than Originality.ai on SEO-content workflow polish, weaker than Turnitin on entrenched academic install base, and the no-public-tier-pricing posture from the homepage is friction. Pick Pangram when accuracy matters more than ecosystem; skip if you just need a casual one-off check.', now()),

-- ── niural-ai → business-finance ────────────────────────────
('Niural AI', 'niural-ai', 'AI-powered HR, payroll, and global Employer of Record platform — unified PEO, global payroll, EOR, and payments natively.', 'Niural is an AI-native HR and payroll platform that unifies US payroll, global Employer of Record (EOR) services, contractor management, benefits administration, and multi-currency international payments under one stack. The product''s distinguishing thesis is that traditional HR / payroll tools wired together via integrations (Deel + Gusto + a benefits broker + a payments processor) can be replaced by one AI-native platform — Niural''s "AI SuperAgents" (including Perry, the payroll automation agent) handle the recurring task layer that finance and people ops typically own. Direct processor integrations support payments; benefits selection and enrollment is a newly-launched module; enterprise FX rates on international transfers undercut typical EOR markups. Niural positions against Deel and Remote (global EOR incumbents), Rippling (HR + IT + finance super-suite), Gusto and Justworks (US-payroll specialists), and Papaya Global (enterprise EOR). The differentiator is "AI-native" framing — most competitors bolt AI on top of legacy payroll engines.', 'https://niural.com', 'contact', '[]'::jsonb, 'intermediate', true, '{"web","api"}', '{"US payroll with automated compliance","Global hiring via Employer of Record (EOR) + local entity payroll","Contractor management with dedicated payment workflows","Benefits selection and enrollment platform","Perry — AI agent for payroll automation","Multi-currency international payments at enterprise FX rates","Direct processor integrations for payments","AI SuperAgents framework across HR + payroll tasks"}', '{"QuickBooks","Xero","Slack","Google Workspace"}', true, '{"Startups and SMBs hiring globally without setting up local entities","Companies consolidating Deel + Gusto + benefits broker into one platform","Finance and people-ops teams wanting AI automation for recurring payroll tasks","Multi-country teams needing FX-efficient cross-border payments"}', '{"US-only single-state payroll (Gusto / Justworks are cheaper and good enough)","Buyers needing transparent public pricing before sales call (Niural is contact-only)","Enterprise multi-thousand-employee global rollouts where Papaya / Rippling have stronger track records","Companies already deep in Rippling or Deel — switching cost outweighs the AI-native pitch"}', 'The AI-native HR + payroll + global EOR consolidation play for startups and SMBs hiring across borders — Niural unifies what Deel + Gusto + a benefits broker typically deliver as separate vendors, with AI SuperAgents (Perry) handling the recurring task layer. The multi-currency payments + enterprise FX positioning is genuinely useful for companies paying contractors abroad. It''s weaker than Deel on global EOR depth and country coverage, weaker than Rippling on the broader IT + finance super-suite play, and the no-public-pricing contact-sales motion is friction. Pick Niural when AI-native automation matters more than an incumbent track record.', now())

